---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../components/CodeBlock.astro';
const pubspec = `dependencies:
  leonard_flutter:
    git: { url: https://github.com/memento-engineering/lenny.git, path: packages/leonard_flutter }
  # optional reference extensions
  leonard_router:
    git: { url: https://github.com/memento-engineering/lenny.git, path: packages/leonard_router }
  leonard_riverpod:
    git: { url: https://github.com/memento-engineering/lenny.git, path: packages/leonard_riverpod }
  leonard_dio:
    git: { url: https://github.com/memento-engineering/lenny.git, path: packages/leonard_dio }`;
const mainDart = `import 'package:leonard_flutter/leonard_flutter.dart';

class MyLeonardApp extends LeonardApp {
  @override
  LeonardAppConfig build() => LeonardAppConfig(
    extensions: [RouterExtension(), RiverpodLeonardExtension(), LeonardDioExtension()],
    app: MaterialApp(home: HomeScreen()),
  );
}

void main() => LeonardBinding.run(MyLeonardApp());`;
const cliCmd = `dart run leonard_cli --goal "open settings and toggle dark mode" --model qwen-mlx
# or: --model claude   |   --model openai`;
---
<Layout title="Getting started — Leonard">
  <div class="container"><h1>Getting started</h1></div>
  <Section id="prereqs" title="Prerequisites">
    <ul>
      <li>A Flutter app you can run in <strong>debug mode</strong>.</li>
      <li>Dart <strong>3.11+</strong>.</li>
      <li>The app reachable over the <strong>VM service</strong> (the default when you <code>flutter run</code> in debug).</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>
  <Section id="add-deps" title="1. Add the packages">
    <CodeBlock code={pubspec} lang="yaml" />
  </Section>
  <Section id="wrap-main" title="2. Wrap main()">
    <p>Implement <code>LeonardApp.build</code> to return a <code>LeonardAppConfig</code> with your extensions and your app, then hand it to <code>LeonardBinding.run</code>:</p>
    <CodeBlock code={mainDart} lang="dart" />
  </Section>
  <Section id="run-cli" title="3a. Drive it from the CLI">
    <CodeBlock code={cliCmd} lang="text" />
    <p>Environment variables:</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Var</th><th>Used by</th><th>Default</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>SWIFT_INFER_ENDPOINT</code></td><td><code>qwen-mlx</code></td><td><code>http://localhost:8080</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>SWIFT_INFER_AGENT_TOKEN</code></td><td><code>qwen-mlx</code></td><td>(none — bearer token, optional)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code></td><td><code>claude</code></td><td>(required)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>OPENAI_API_KEY</code></td><td><code>openai</code></td><td>(required)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </Section>
  <Section id="run-devtools" title="3b. Or drive it from DevTools">
    <p>Open DevTools for the running app &rarr; the <strong>Leonard</strong> tab &rarr; type your goal &rarr; <strong>Start</strong>. Watch the model's reasoning in <strong>Thinking</strong> and each observed/acted step in <strong>Timeline</strong>.</p>
  </Section>
  <Section id="next" title="What next">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/memento-engineering/lenny/blob/main/docs/extension_authoring_guide.md">Write an extension</a> for your own router / state / networking layer.</li>
      <li>Read the <a href="https://github.com/memento-engineering/lenny/blob/main/docs/leonard_prd_v0.5.md">PRD</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>
</Layout>
